{{see|Bud}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
*bŭd, /bʌd/, /<tt>bVd</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ʌd|Rhymes: -ʌd]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A newly formed leaf or flower that has not yet unfolded.
#: ''After a long, cold winter, the trees finally began to produce buds.''
# (''slang'') Potent cannabis taken from the flowering part of the plant. <!-- Is that exactly right? Not in my direct realm of experience . . . -->
#: ''Want to smoke some bud?''
# A small rounded body in the process of splitting from an organism, which may grow into a genetically identical new organism. <!-- what a boggart! -->
#: ''In this slide, you can see a yeast cell forming buds.''
# (''slang'') [[Buddy]].
#: ''I like to hang out with my buds on Saturday night.''

